data.body:
I have a problem with unmanaged memory leak in Windows Store Universal App. 
Here are steps to reproduce the problem:
1) Create Universal project from MonoGame template
2) Add blank page for Windows 8.1 project and button to it

``` xaml
        <Button Content="Go forward" Click="ButtonBase_OnClick"/>
```

``` csharp
        private void ButtonBase_OnClick(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
        {
            var gamePage = new GamePage(string.Empty);
            Window.Current.Content = gamePage;
        }
```

3) Modify app.xaml.cs

``` csharp
        protected override void OnLaunched(LaunchActivatedEventArgs args)
        {
            var blankPage = new BlankPage();
            Window.Current.Content = blankPage;
            Window.Current.Activate();
        }
```

4) Add a button to game page 

``` xaml
<SwapChainBackgroundPanel
    x:Class="MonoTest.GamePage"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:local="using:MonoTest"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    mc:Ignorable="d">

    <Grid >
        <Button Click="GoBackBtnClicked" Content="Start game"/>
    </Grid>
</SwapChainBackgroundPanel>
```

``` csharp
        private void GoBackBtnClicked(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
        {
            var blankPage = new BlankPage();
            Window.Current.Content = blankPage;
        }
```

Here what I can see in profiler: 
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4506967/7794076/42bd76da-02cf-11e5-9f62-8d3ad27fbc82.png)
Unmanaged memory allocations are done on navigation to game page. 

I tried to call Dispose for game 

``` csharp
        public GamePage(string launchArguments)
        {
            this.InitializeComponent();
            // Create the game.

            _game = XamlGame<Game1>.Create(launchArguments, Window.Current.CoreWindow, this);
            Unloaded += OnUnloaded;
        }

        private void OnUnloaded(object sender, RoutedEventArgs routedEventArgs)
        {
            _game.Dispose();
        }
```

But this code throws ObjectDisposedException

```
    System.ObjectDisposedException: The Game1 object was used after being Disposed.
    Object name: 'Game1'.
       at Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Game.AssertNotDisposed()
       at Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Game.DoUpdate(GameTime gameTime)
       at Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Game.Tick()
       at Microsoft.Xna.Framework.MetroGameWindow.Tick()
       at Microsoft.Xna.Framework.MetroGamePlatform.<StartRunLoop>b__0(Object o, Object a)
```

Can please anyone help me with this problem?

PS I'm using MonoGame 3.4

In my game I am using huge amount of assets and I need to manage them. I have multiple content managers, each for one level. When I unload all loaded assets:

```
   Content.Unload();
   Content.Dispose();
```

and after that try to load Effect I get old disposed instance. Models and textures are loaded correctly. I am using Windows OpenGL version with current source. Any ideas?
